card-text.text-dark 1. Performing personal care needs after given a patient's assignment and attending to his/her requests promptly. if unable to perform a certain task, report to the primary care nurse immediately.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 2. Meeting safety needs of patient and using equipment safety and properly (foot stools,side rails, 02 etc.).      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 3. Giving personal care including baths, back rubs, oral hygiene, shampoos and charging bed linen as often as assigned.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 4. Assisting in feeding the patient as assigned.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 5. Planning and preparing nutritious meals including shopping, as assigned      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 6. Assisting in feeding the patient as assigned.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 7. Taking and recording oral, rectal and axillary temperatures, pulse respiration and blood pressure when ordered with appropriate completed / demonstrated skills compentency.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 8. Providing proper care and observation of patient's skin prevent breakdown of tissue over bony prominence.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 9. Reporting on patient's condition and significant changes to the assigned supervisory nurse. also aware of the caregiver or other individuals living with the patient and interpersonal issues.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 10. Assisting in abulation and exercise as instructed by the primary care nurse or therapist      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 11. Listing driver with automobile that is insured in accordance with organization requirements and is in going working order.    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-12            h4.text-dark Job Limitations        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text The Hospice Aide will not function in any manner viewed as the practice of nursing according to the nurse practice act. Specifically, the Hospice Aide will not administer medications. take physicians order or perform procedures requiring the training. Knowledge and skill of a licensed nurse, such as sterile techniques.    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-12          h4.text-dark Skills Required        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 1. Good in oral and written communications.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 2. Good Organization skills    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-12          h4.text-dark Working Conditions        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 1. Community home environment        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 2. Exposure to infectious diseases.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 3. In and out of automobile.    br    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-6            label.text-dark Name of applicants            input.form-control.waves-float.text-capitalize.text-dark(type='text' value= (app)? app.pg5nameofapplicants : '' name='pg5nameofapplicants' )        .form-group.col-md-6            .card                .card-body.bg-whi